definitions.definition: ( British , military , aviation ) Of fighter aircraft : to fire at a target opportunistically .

main_definition: ( British , military , aviation ) Of fighter aircraft : to fire at a target opportunistically .

definitions.definition: Of an actor in a film, stage play, etc.: to repeat the word rhubarb to create the sound of indistinct conversation; hence , to converse indistinctly , to mumble .
To articulate indistinctly or mumble ( words or phrases ); to say inconsequential or vague things because one does not know what to say, or to stall for time .

main_definition: ( intransitive , originally theater ) Of an actor in a film, stage play, etc.: to repeat the word rhubarb to create the sound of indistinct conversation; hence , to converse indistinctly , to mumble .
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To articulate indistinctly or mumble ( words or phrases ); to say inconsequential or vague things because one does not know what to say, or to stall for time .
